26/12/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police detained Budva Mayor Rajko Kuljaca and Deputy Mayor Dragan Marovic on Friday (December 24th), reportedly for suspected abuse of office, stemming from illegal construction on a cape near the coastal town. 
Eight other officials from Budva Municipality were also arrested. 
Dragan Marovic is the brother of Deputy Prime Minister Svetozar Marovic, who resigned on December 21st, along with Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic. 
(RTCG, Portal Analitika, Pcnen, Beta - 24/12/10)
